I have run a benchmark on `Vector{String}` (which is a worst case for the new algorithm) and I get:
on 0.22.5 (after compilation)
```julia&gt; df1 = DataFrame(id = string.(1:20*10^6), x=1:20*10^6);

julia&gt; allowmissing!(df1, :id);

julia&gt; df1.id[1:2:end] .= missing;

julia&gt; df2 = DataFrame(id=string.(rand(1:20*10^6, 500_000)), y=1:500_000);

julia&gt; @time leftjoin(df1, df2, on=:id, matchmissing=:equal);
 26.274402 seconds (228 allocations: 1.988 GiB, 2.58% gc time)```
on `main` (after compilation):
```julia&gt; df1 = DataFrame(id = string.(1:20*10^6), x=1:20*10^6);

julia&gt; allowmissing!(df1, :id);

julia&gt; df1.id[1:2:end] .= missing;

julia&gt; df2 = DataFrame(id=string.(rand(1:20*10^6, 500_000)), y=1:500_000);

julia&gt; @time leftjoin(df1, df2, on=:id, matchmissing=:equal);
  2.444262 seconds (253 allocations: 686.812 MiB, 21.19% gc time)```
but maybe your data has a different structure?

